HEADWORD: Demountable
<hw>De*mount"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[See <er>De-</er>;
<er>Mount</er>.]</ety> <def>Capable of being dismounted; -- said of a
form of rim, for an automobile wheel, which can be removed with its tire
from the wheel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

